ProductSource 1 -- * SupplierOrderLineItem
A SupplierOrderLineItem has A ProductSource. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one ProductSource.
A ProductSource has some SupplierOrderLineItems. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a SupplierOrderLineItem is created, its ProductSource must be assigned. When a SupplierOrderLineItem is deleted, its ProductSource is not deleted and its list of SupplierOrderLineItems is decreased. When a ProductSource is deleted, its SupplierOrderLineItems are not deleted. They are assigned to another ProductSource.
